Selling goods and services online
Facial Images
We may provide you with entertainment services, like Luxand BabyMaker, or our remote API services. You may submit submit digital photographs, which may contain images your face, to such services. Such services allow you to get personalized entertainment pictures based on the pictures you upload to them. For example, the BabyMaker & Pregnancy Tracker app allows you to upload the images of your face and get an image of what your baby may look like. The faces are sent to the servers of Luxand, Inc. These servers analyze and transform them into an image of a baby, which is sent back to the app. Our applications do not store your faces on your device unless explicitly asked to do so. The faces and baby pictures may be stored on the servers of Luxand, Inc. located in the United States, solely for the purpose of providing you with the outlined services. Your uploaded faces are not shared with any third parties except as with hosting providers, such as Amazon Web Services, Google Cloud or IBM Cloud Services. We do not store the faces longer than needed to provide you with the outlined services. To request the deletion of your face data or baby pictures, please contact us at info@luxand.com.
This processing constitutes:
a Sharing in California
Luxand FaceSDK
When you download and use Luxand FaceSDK or products that may include Luxand FaceSDK, we may automatically collect the following information about your device, for the purposes of activating the usage of Luxand products, including Luxand FaceSDK, and the products that may employ Luxand FaceSDK: the type of your device; the name and version of your operating system; the "hardware identifier" of your device; your IP address; the license key you're using to activate Luxand FaceSDK; other Luxand license keys; the information about software and hardware configuration of your devices.
This processing constitutes:
a Sharing in California
Mobile Applications
When you download and use our Products, we automatically collect information on the type of device you use, operating system version, the device identifier (or “UDID”), the advertising identifier (or “IDFA”) and AppsFlyer ID. We also use Facebook SDK and AppsFlyer SDK to collect analytics about the usage of the app.
This processing constitutes:
a Sale in California
a Sharing in California
Passive Liveness Open Beta Test
When you join the passive liveness beta test available on the https://liveness.luxand.com/ page, we collect your uploaded photos (including real and fake images) to use them in passive liveness algorithm tests and to potentially improve the algorithm in general. Uploaded photos are saved and analyzed by us and our affiliates only for passive liveness test and algorithm improvement purposes and are not used in any other way.
Before uploading your photos, you will be asked to (i) read our privacy policy and (ii) provide your explicit consent to the processing of your photos for the said purpose. Your consent is the legal basis on which we rely when processing your photos. To make sure that your photos are properly protected, we treat them as your personal data. We store your photos in our servers located in the United States. We do not transfer or disclose your photos to any third parties, unless it is necessary for their purposes. We do not sell your photos. We make sure that our data processors that come into contact with your photos provide an adequate level of protection to your photos. The list of our data processors is provided in this privacy policy - please see the "Hosting and backend infrastructure" section. We do not associate uploaded photos with any other personal data (such as your name and email address), however, we may associate uploaded photos with technical parameters of your browser or device (device type, camera type, browser type and more). Such aggregated data will be treated as personal data.
We implement industry-appropriate security measures to protect your personal data (such as access limitation, secured networks, encryption, and anonymization). We will store your photos in our systems as long as they are necessary for the above-mentioned purposes. As soon as your photos are no longermore necessary or we do not have a legal basis for storing and using them, we will securely delete your photos from our systems. If you would like us to limit or stop any further processing of your photos, you can limit or withdraw your consent at any time by contacting us at info@luxand.com and explaining your request in detail. If, after receiving your request, we can identify your photos on the basis of the details provided by you, we will delete them from our systems and limit or cease any further processing of your photos. However, please keep in mind that your photos are saved with no other personal details, therefore, we may not be able to identify your photos, even if you request it. We will inform you within 30 days from the receipt of your request whether your consent can be withdrawn.
Should you have any further questions about our Passive Liveness Open Beta Test, please do not hesitate to contact us at info@luxand.com.
This processing constitutes:
a Sharing in California
